<!-- SECTION 4: WHO CAN FILE -->
<section class="content-section" id="who-section">
    <div class="content-container">
        <div class="text-content">
            <h2 class="section-title">Which E-Commerce Models Need Which Registrations</h2>
            <div class="content-text">
                
                <p>The right registration stack depends on the business model. Patron e-commerce business registration is HIGH-VALUE for:</p>
                <ul>
                    <li><strong>D2C founders building brand pages with own checkout:</strong> Need entity, GST, Trademark and Consumer Rules compliance from day one - inter-state supply trigger means GST is rarely optional even at low turnover.</li>
                    <li><strong>Marketplace sellers planning INR 50 lakh+ annual GMV:</strong> The cash flow drag from TCS plus the marketplace seller registration overhead justifies professional setup.</li>
                    <li><strong>Marketplace operators / aggregators (platform builders):</strong> The multi-state Section 24(x) registration alone is non-trivial; Form REG-07 with Rule 12(1A) multi-state declarations is essential.</li>
                    <li><strong>Cross-border e-commerce founders:</strong> Selling to GCC, US, Europe via Shopify, Amazon Global or Etsy - IEC, RBI LRS considerations, FEMA compliance add complexity.</li>
                    <li><strong>Food e-commerce founders:</strong> D2C food brands, cloud kitchens, food aggregators - FSSAI license plus Section 9(5) deemed supplier rules require specialised handling.</li>
                    <li><strong>FDI-backed e-commerce platforms:</strong> Press Note 2 of 2018 marketplace model restrictions must be designed in at entity setup, not retrofitted post-funding.</li>
                </ul>
                <p style="margin-top:16px;"><strong>Limited value for:</strong> Casual sellers / hobbyists with annual GMV under INR 10-15 lakh selling only on a single marketplace; pure dropshipping businesses with no inventory holding (FDI marketplace model rules + GST place-of-supply complications need a separate strategy session); subscription-only digital services / SaaS (not e-commerce in the Section 2(45) sense).</p>

            </div>
            </div>
        </div>
    </div>
</section>

<!-- SECTION 5: OUR SERVICES -->
<section class="content-section" id="services-section">
    <div class="content-container">
        <div class="text-content">
            <h2 class="section-title">Patron Accounting Ecommerce Services - Delhi</h2>
            <div class="content-text">
                <div class="table-responsive-wrapper">
                <table>
                    <thead><tr><th>Service</th><th>What We Do</th></tr></thead>
                    <tbody>
                        <tr><td>Business Model Strategy and Registration Plan</td><td>One-week strategy memo selecting the right model (D2C / Marketplace Seller / Marketplace Operator / Section 9(5) Aggregator); recommending entity type based on FDI intent, ESOP plans and growth trajectory; mapping the full registration stack with sequencing and dependencies.</td></tr>
                        <tr><td>Entity Setup (Pvt Ltd or LLP)</td><td>For Pvt Ltd - SPICe+ on MCA21 v3 with MOA, AOA, AGILE-PRO-S (auto-allotment of PAN, TAN, GSTIN, EPFO, ESIC); for LLP - FiLLiP with LLP Agreement and Form 3; Certificate of Incorporation in 7-10 working days.</td></tr>
                        <tr><td>GST Registration (Section 24 Framework)</td><td>Form GST REG-01 for standard sellers; Form GST REG-07 for marketplace operators collecting TCS under Section 52; multi-state registration using Rule 12(1A); HSN code mapping for product categories.</td></tr>
                        <tr><td>Brand Protection - Trademark and Copyright</td><td>Trademark search across categories; Form TM-A filing in 1 primary class (with 50% rebate at INR 2,250 per class for DPIIT-recognised startups); copyright registration for original content; domain protection guidance.</td></tr>
                        <tr><td>Sectoral Licences (IEC, FSSAI, Udyam)</td><td>IEC via DGFT portal for cross-border (5-10 days); FSSAI Basic / State / Central via FoSCoS portal for food (30-60 days); Udyam / MSME via Udyam portal (same day, free); Delhi Shop and Establishment via Delhi Labour Department.</td></tr>
                        <tr><td>Consumer Protection Rules 2020 + IT Rules 2021 Compliance Package</td><td>Privacy Policy, Terms and Conditions, Refund / Return / Cancellation Policy, Cookie Policy drafted; Grievance Officer and Nodal Officer appointment letters; IT Rules 2021 intermediary compliance documentation; DPDP Act 2023 privacy notice template; first-cycle compliance audit.</td></tr>

                    </tbody>
                </table>
                </div>
            </div>
        </div>
    </div>
</section>

