<!-- SECTION 15A: LEGAL FRAMEWORK -->
<section class="content-section">
    <div class="content-container">
        <div class="text-content">
            <h2 class="section-title">Legal and Compliance Framework</h2>
            <div class="content-text">
                
                <p><strong>Entity Setup Statute:</strong> Companies Act 2013 (Pvt Ltd via SPICe+); LLP Act 2008 (LLP via FiLLiP); both on MCA21 v3.</p>
                <p><strong>Core GST Statute:</strong> Central Goods and Services Tax Act 2017 read with CGST Rules 2017; SGST Act of respective State.</p>
                <p><strong>GST Registration - ECO:</strong> Section 24(x) CGST Act 2017 - mandatory registration for every E-Commerce Operator regardless of turnover; in each State or UT of operations.</p>
                <p><strong>GST Threshold - Goods Sellers through ECO:</strong> Notification 34/2023-Central Tax dated 31 July 2023 - registration only if aggregate turnover exceeds INR 40 lakh (INR 20 lakh for special category states: Manipur, Mizoram, Nagaland, Tripura, Sikkim, Arunachal Pradesh, Meghalaya, Uttarakhand, Puducherry, Telangana).</p>
                <p><strong>GST Threshold - Service Sellers through ECO:</strong> Notification 65/2017-Central Tax dated 15 November 2017 - exempt from registration if turnover under INR 20 lakh (INR 10 lakh for special category states); Section 9(5) services excluded.</p>
                <p><strong>TCS (Tax Collected at Source):</strong> Section 52 CGST Act 2017 - TCS at 0.50% (0.25% CGST + 0.25% SGST/UTGST or 0.50% IGST) on net value of taxable supplies; effective from 10 July 2024 per Notification 15/2024-Central Tax (reduced from earlier 1%).</p>
                <p><strong>Section 9(5) Deemed Supplier:</strong> CGST Act Section 9(5) read with Notification 17/2017-Central Tax (Rate) - cab aggregators, accommodation booking, housekeeping, restaurant services through food delivery platforms.</p>
                <p><strong>Penalty Provisions:</strong> Section 122 CGST Act - 100% of tax due OR INR 10,000 (whichever higher) for operating without registration; Section 122(1B) - specific to ECO TCS default, retrospective effect from 1 October 2023.</p>
                <p><strong>Consumer Protection:</strong> Consumer Protection Act 2019 read with Consumer Protection (E-Commerce) Rules 2020 notified by Ministry of Consumer Affairs on 23 July 2020.</p>
                <p><strong>Intermediary Compliance:</strong> Information Technology Act 2000 read with IT (Intermediary Guidelines and Digital Media Ethics Code) Rules 2021 notified on 25 February 2021.</p>
                <p><strong>Data Protection:</strong> Digital Personal Data Protection Act 2023 notified 11 August 2023; phased implementation through 2026.</p>
                <p><strong>FDI Policy:</strong> Press Note 2 (2018 series) by DPIIT dated 26 December 2018 - FDI in e-commerce permitted only in marketplace model; inventory model prohibited.</p>
                <p><strong>Cross-Border:</strong> Foreign Trade (Development and Regulation) Act 1992 - IEC mandatory; managed by DGFT.</p>
                <p><strong>Food E-Commerce:</strong> Food Safety and Standards Act 2006 read with FSS Regulations - FSSAI license (Basic / State / Central); FoSCoS portal.</p>
                <p><strong>Authority for source verification:</strong> MCA21 v3 at <a href="https://www.mca.gov.in" target="_blank" rel="noopener">mca.gov.in</a>, GST portal at <a href="https://www.gst.gov.in" target="_blank" rel="noopener">gst.gov.in</a> and DGFT at <a href="https://www.dgft.gov.in" target="_blank" rel="noopener">dgft.gov.in</a>.</p>

            </div>
        </div>
    </div>
</section>

